  "prompt": "How has legislation evolved to combat money laundering?",
  "response": "Legislation to combat money laundering has evolved significantly over the past few decades:\n\n1. Early Developments\n- Bank Secrecy Act (1970) in the US\n- First international framework by Financial Action Task Force (FATF) in 1989\n- Initial focus on reporting large cash transactions\n\n2. Key Milestones\n- Money Laundering Control Act (1986)\n- USA PATRIOT Act (2001) after 9/11\n- Expanded regulations for financial institutions\n- Increased international cooperation\n\n3. Modern Approaches\n- Enhanced customer due diligence requirements\n- Stricter Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations\n- Cryptocurrency transaction monitoring\n- Beneficial ownership transparency\n- Increased cross-border information sharing\n\n4. Recent Technological Adaptations\n- Advanced digital tracking systems\n- AI and machine learning for detecting suspicious transactions\n- Blockchain analysis tools\n- Real-time transaction monitoring\n\n5. Global Compliance Trends\n- Harmonized international standards\n- Increasingly severe penalties\n- Mandatory risk assessments\n- Comprehensive compliance programs\n- Regular regulatory audits\n\nThese legislative developments reflect growing complexity in financial systems and sophisticated money laundering techniques.",
